[[File:Charles Edward Boutibonne A Warm Reception.jpg|thumb|Édouard Boutibonne, ''A Warm Reception'', oil on panel, 55x43 cm, 1868]]
'''Charles Édouard Boutibonne''' ([[Budapest]], 8 July 1816 &ndash; [[Wilderswil]], 7 February 1897) was a French painter of the [[academic classicism]] school.

He was born to French parents in Hungary.<ref>Explication des ouvrages de peinture sculpture, architecture xxiii  Société des artistes français pour l'exposition des Beaux Arts - 1869 -"BOUTIBONNE (Charles-Édouard), né à Pesth, de parents français , méd. 3° cl. 1847  "</ref> As a 22-year-old he painted a portrait of [[Liszt]].<ref>Lamennais: exposition organisée pour le centième anniversaire de ... Bibliothèque nationale (France), Bibliothèque nationale (France) - 1954 "Franz Liszt, par Édouard Boutibonne, 1838"</ref> He was a student of [[Franz Winterhalter]].<ref>Empress Eugénie and the Arts:  p 103 Alison McQueen - 2011 "One instance involved Hungarianborn Charles Edouard Boutibonne, a student of Winterhalter, from whom Queen Victoria commissioned Eugénie, Empress of France ( figure 2.12)."</ref> 
