'''Personal imaging''' is the continuous [[real time (media)|realtime]] capturing, archiving, recording,
and sharing of personal [[experience]] through [[image]]s. Typically the images are accompanied by other media such as [[sound reproduction|audio]]visual streams, or with [[writing|text]]ual narratives such as [[diary|diaries]], and often in an interactive way, i.e. people viewing the images comment on the images in realtime while they are being captured, so as to influence the capture process.{{Citation needed|date=August 2009}}

{{DEFAULTSORT:Personal Imaging}}
[[Category:Art genres]]


{{Art-stub}}

{{Use DMY dates|date=September 2017}} The '''Raigam Tele'es Best Teledrama Editor Award''' is presented annually in Sri Lanka by the Kingdom of Raigam associated with many commercial brands for the best Sri Lankan editor of the year in television screen.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.srilankanewslive.com/news/security/item/12553-it-s-tele-es-time-again |title=It’s Tele’es time again! |publisher=Srilankanewslive.com |accessdate=11 March 2017}}</ref>
The award was first given in 2005. Following is a list of the winners of this prestigious title since then.
==Award list in each year== {| class="wikitable" |- ! Year !! Best Editor !! Teledrama |- | 2005 || || |- | 2006 || || |- | 2007 || || |- | 2008 || || |- | 2009 || || |- | 2010 || Tharanga Kumarasinghe || ''Arungal''<ref>{{cite web|title=Raigam Tele'es 2009 award winners|url=http://www.sarasaviya.lk/2010/05/13/_art.asp?fn=sa10051314&pn=16|publisher=Sarasaviya}}</ref> |- | 2011 || Jagath Weeratunga || <ref>{{cite web|title=Raigam Tele'es 2010 award winners|url=http://www.sarasaviya.lk/2011/05/26/_art.asp?fn=sa11052613&pn=20|publisher=Sarasaviya}}</ref> |- | 2012 || Himal Dharmaratne || ''Athkanda Lihiniya''<ref>{{cite web|title=Raigam Tele'es 2011 award winners|url=http://www.sarasaviya.lk/2012/05/17/?fn=sa1205178|publisher=Sarasaviya}}</ref> |- | 2013 || Lakruwan de Seram || ''Piyavi''<ref>{{cite web|title=Raigam Tele'es 2012 award winners|url=http://www.sarasaviya.lk/2013/05/23/?fn=sa1305232|publisher=Sarasaviya}}</ref> |- | 2014 || Jagath Weeratunga || ''Appachchi''<ref>{{cite web|title=Raigam Tele'es 2013 award winners|url=http://www.sarasaviya.lk/2014/06/12/?fn=sa1406122|publisher=Sarasaviya}}</ref> |- | 2015 || Jagath Weeratunga || ''Chess''<ref>{{cite web|title=Raigam Tele'es 2014 award winners|url=http://www.sarasaviya.lk/2015/06/18/?fn=sa1506186|publisher=Sarasaviya}}</ref> |- | 2016 || Himal Dharmaratne || ''[[Daskon (TV series)|Daskon]]''<ref>{{cite web|title=Raigam Tele'es 2015 award winners|url=http://www.sarasaviya.lk/2016/06/09/?fn=sa16060915|publisher=Sarasaviya}}</ref> |- | 2017 || Indika Jayawardena || ''One Way''<ref>{{cite web|title=Raigam Tele'es 2016 award winners|url=http://www.sarasaviya.lk/2017/06/29/?fn=sa1706298|publisher=Sarasaviya}}</ref> |- | 2018 || Jagath Weeratunga || ''Badde Kulawamiya''<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sarasaviya.lk/2018/03/29/?fn=sa1803299 |title=Raigam Tele'es 2017 award winners |publisher=Sarasaviya |accessdate=29 March 2018}}</ref> |}
